-- Fast Retailing Shares Poised to Fall After Domestic Uniqlo Sales Decline
-- Kyung Bok Cho
-- 2010-07-04T23:52:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-04/fast-retailing-shares-poised-to-fall-after-domestic-uniqlo-sales-decline.html

          
          
             Fast Retailing Co. shares were poised
to fall in Tokyo trading after the Japanese retailer said
domestic sales at its Uniqlo casual clothing chain declined 5.8
percent in June from a year earlier.  
 The shares were bid at 12,680 yen as of 8:51 a.m. on the
Tokyo Stock Exchange, compared with the July 2 closing price of
13,430 yen.  
          
          


  


        